docs.snippet: The Senate voted on Monday to repeal the 4 per cent dividend tax credit on dividends exceeding $50 a year. The action came after Senator Lyndon B. Johnson of Texas, the Democratic majority leader, was able to switch two votes to save the amendment by...
docs.lead_paragraph: The Senate voted on Monday to repeal the 4 per cent dividend tax credit on dividends exceeding $50 a year. The action came after Senator Lyndon B. Johnson of Texas, the Democratic majority leader, was able to switch two votes to save the amendment by a 42 to 41 vote.
